The paper deals with catastrophic forgetting in deep neural networks, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on visual classification datasets, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also proposes a new experimental protocol and discusses potential solutions, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
